description:
&lt;p&gt;The role of a Patient Coordinator is varied, with the department spanning Reception, Outpatient appointments, Ward Clerks and our Call Centre. You will have a primary function of a Reception role but will have the opportunity to learn all functions ensuring that no day is ever the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have customer services experience, be able to demonstrate good communication and organisational skills and have an empathetic approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;24 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date of 16th November subject to change dependent on the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leanne White&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01305 255391&lt;/p&gt;
